Owen da Gama will take charge of the team in the international friendly match against Mozambique on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG Bafana Bafana Head Coach Ephraim Shakes Mashaba will not join the team on their trip to Mozambique as the South African Football Association (Safa) has deemed it necessary to employ disciplinary measures after a regrettable incident at Peter Mokaba Stadium on Saturday.Bafana Bafana coach Shakes Mashaba to face disciplinary action from SAFA after regrettable incident at Peter Mokaba Stadium @DChimhavi pic.twitter.com/taSPkg1ocUAssistant Coach Owen da Gama will take charge of the team in the above-mentioned international friendly match against Mozambique on Tuesday, 15 November 2016 in Maputo.Assistant coach Owen da Gama will take charge of the team in a friendly match against Mozambique on Tuesday @DChimhavi pic.twitter.com/d5G0cVj0szThe association says it will not be making any further comments on the matter out of respect for the dignity of the head coach, Safa and the legally privileged nature of such proceedings.On Saturday, Bafana Bafana bounced back with a 2-1 win over Senegal in their 2018 World Cup Qualifier in Polokwane on Saturday.Mashaba s troop headed into the match exactly a year since they last won a competitive match at home following a draw against Burkina Faso.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)